#Train Test Split #80-20 split
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# Separate features and target variable
X = data1.drop(['TARGET'],axis=1)
Y = data1['TARGET']


# split: 80% train and 20% test
X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state=181)

print("Training set shape:", X_train.shape)

Handling Imbalance data: Earlier we noticed that there is an imbalance in sample data that we took to train our model, it's more baised towards 0 class as we noticed in the confusion matrix and as well as we cross-checked it using value_counts function. Now we have maintained that imbalance by separating the 0 and 1 class in TARGET and taken sample from each class and we concatenated again into the target variable. To do that we first merged the features and target in train data and after taking samples from each class, we assigned the features to X and TARGET to Y and splitted the dataset.

# Define the model evaluation function
def model_eval(X_sample):
    X_sample_df = pd.DataFrame(X_sample, columns=X_train.columns)
    y_pred_prob = classifier.predict_proba(X_sample_df)[:, 1]
    return y_pred_prob

# Define the problem
problem = {
    'num_vars': X_train.shape[1],
    'names': X_train.columns.tolist(),
    'bounds': [[0, 1]] * X_train.shape[1]
}

# Generate samples

# Evaluate the model for each sample

Inference from Sensitivity Analysis

  1. Big Influence on Target:
  • TRANS_COUNT_ATM_PRC (S1: 0.2784) and AMOUNT_RUB_ATM_PRC (S1: 0.2004) have large influences on the target variable, so these features are key predictors

TURNOVER_PAYM (S1: 0.2037) and REST_AVG_PAYM (S1: 0.1412) are also influential

  1. Low or No Influence on Target:
  • It has no influence on the target variable: CR_PROD_CNT_PIL, TURNOVER_CC, CR_PROD_CNT_CC, REST_DYNAMIC_FDEP_3M, REST_DYNAMIC_IL_1M, CR_PROD_CNT_CCFP and LDEAL_GRACE_DAYS_PCT_MED (S1: 0.0). These features look not helpful for the predictive model

Very small negative impacts on the target variable are given by CNT_TRAN_MED_TEND while TRANS_COUNT_ATM_PRC and AMOUNT_RUB_ATM_PRC have higher confidence levels of the impact on the target, such as 0.1322 and 0.1299, respectively. Thus, they are more reliable estimates. columns with zero impacts on the target also have zero confidence. They become not useful in predicting the target variable and hence can be considered insignificant.

  1. Impact on Other Columns:
  • Apart from the target column itself, TRANS_COUNT_ATM_PRC and TURNOVER_PAYM both have large impacts on the other columns, with S2 values of 0.3096 and 0.2017 respectively. It may be that there is some relation between these two variables and others in the dataset.

Columns like CR_PROD_CNT_PIL and TURNOVER_CC have little or no influence on other columns

  1. Mixed Influence:

SUM_TRAN_MED_TEND and CNT_TRAN_CLO_TENDENCY3M show some possibility of an impact on the target and other columns but with a varying confidence level.

TRANS_COUNT_ATM_PRC and TURNOVER_PAYM also significantly impact other columns (S2: 0.3096 and 0.2017 respectively). It might indicate relationships between these features and others in the dataset Columns like CR_PROD_CNT_PIL and TURNOVER_CC have minimal or zero impact on other columns

Mixed Influence: SUM_TRAN_MED_TENDENCY3M and CNT_TRAN_CLO_TENDENCY3M show some posibility of an impact on the target and other columns but with a varying confidence level
